  "prompt": "What instrument is used to measure volume?",
  "response": "There are several instruments used to measure volume, depending on the form of the material being measured:\n\n1. **Graduated Cylinder**: Commonly used in laboratories to measure the volume of liquids.\n2. **Measuring Cup**: Often used in cooking and baking for measuring liquid and dry ingredients.\n3. **Volumetric Flask**: Used in chemistry for precise volume measurements of liquids.\n4. **Pipette**: Used to measure and transfer small volumes of liquids.\n5. **Syringe**: Often used in medical and laboratory settings to measure liquid volumes accurately.\n6. **Water Displacement Method**: For measuring the volume of irregularly shaped solids, where the volume of water displaced by the object is measured.\n7. **Calipers**: Can be used to measure the dimensions of an object to calculate its volume, particularly for solids.\n\nEach of these instruments is suitable for different contexts and types of materials.",
